testcase.name: firewallmanager on redhat should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Class[stdlib]
firewallmanager on redhat should contain File[/etc/sysconfig/firewallmanager]
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Resources[firewall] with purge => false
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Firewall[000 accept all icmp] with proto => "icmp"
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Class[firewall]
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Class[firewallmanager::pre] with allow_icmp => true and allow_localhost => true
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Firewall[001 accept all to lo interface] with proto => "all", iniface => "lo" and action => "accept"
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Firewall[002 reject local traffic not on loopback interface] with action => "reject"
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Firewall[003 accept related established rules] with action => "accept"
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Class[firewallmanager::post] with block_default => true
firewallmanager on redhat should contain Firewall[999 drop all] with proto => "all" and action => "drop"
firewallmanager on debian should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager on debian should contain Notify[UNSUPPORTED OS]
firewallmanager::post on oraclelinux-7-x86_64 should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager::post on scientific-7-x86_64 should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager::post on centos-7-x86_64 should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager::post on redhat-7-x86_64 should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager::pre on oraclelinux-7-x86_64 should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager::pre on scientific-7-x86_64 should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager::pre on centos-7-x86_64 should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
firewallmanager::pre on redhat-7-x86_64 should compile into a catalogue without dependency cycles
